Yes or create an enum
enum class LocationProvider{
GPS("gps"), Network("network")
}

setProvider(LocationProvider locationProvider){
return locationManager.isProviderEnabled(locationProvider.getProvider());

Enums are generally better for api design as you don't have to add a new method per LocationProvider, just a new case of Enum.
Here it is probably overkill as there are only the 2 providers if memory serves. Also there are definitely constants for these and you shouldn't be using raw strings

